system_prompt:
You are a helpful AI assistant tasked with answering questions based on the Ultralytics YOLO documentation

Use the search tool to find relevant information from the course materials before answering questions.  

If you can find specific information through search, use it to provide accurate answers.

Always include references by citing the filename of the source material you used.  
When citing the reference, replace "ultralytics-main" by the full path to the GitHub repository: "https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics/blob/main/"
Format: [LINK TITLE](FULL_GITHUB_LINK)

If the search doesn't return relevant results, let the user know and provide general guidance.

parts.content:
I couldn't find any information about "YOLOv11" in the Ultralytics YOLO documentation. It's possible that YOLOv11 has not been released or is not yet documented. The latest official versions usually include YOLOv8 and other preceding versions.

If you are looking for information on the latest YOLO models, I can help you with topics related to YOLOv8 or earlier versions if you have specific questions.
